+## Web
+
+`hive web` starts the Rails web UI in the foreground. It defaults to `127.0.0.1:4567`, resolves loopback `web.auth_mode: auto` to no-auth local mode, and refuses unauthenticated non-loopback binds unless `web.unsafe_no_auth: true` or `--unsafe-no-auth` is explicit. Non-loopback `auto` uses the existing GitHub device-flow owner gate.
+
+```bash
+hive web
+hive web --port 4570
+hive web install
+hive web start
+hive web status --json
+hive web stop
+```
+
+`hive web install` and `hive web start` manage a separate `hive-web` systemd-user or launchd service. The web service runs foreground `hive web` under the supervisor; it does not replace or merge with the daemon service. Docker/hivebox remains the hosted/public-bind path and keeps the GitHub owner flow.
+
 ## Bot And TUI
 
 `hive tui` opens the terminal dashboard for humans. `hive bot start|stop|status|reload|tail|install` runs the Telegram surface for human-input gates. Both read the same state as the CLI; the TUI intentionally rejects `--json`. `hive bot install [--force] [--json]` installs and enables a per-user autostart service for the bot (systemd-user on Linux, launchd on macOS) so it survives reboot/login — opt-in, mirroring `hive daemon install`; the token comes from `~/.config/hive/.env`, and `hive uninstall` removes the service.
